Step.SQLStatement: create or replace view RV_BankInfo as select b.ad_client_ID, b.ad_Org_ID, b.name, ba.accountno, bd.paymentrule, ba.c_bankaccount_ID, ba.created, ba.createdby, ba.updated, ba.updatedby, ba.UUID, ba.isactive, b.banktype, ba.c_bank_ID, bd.currentnext, ba.accountNo AS info, bd.c_bankaccountdoc_id from c_bankaccount ba inner join c_bank b on ba.c_bank_ID = b.c_bank_ID left join c_bankaccountdoc bd on ba.c_bankaccount_ID = bd.c_bankaccount_ID

create or replace view RV_BankInfo as select b.ad_client_ID, b.ad_Org_ID, b.name, ba.accountno, bd.paymentrule, ba.c_bankaccount_ID, ba.created, ba.createdby, ba.updated, ba.updatedby, ba.UUID, ba.isactive, b.banktype, ba.c_bank_ID, bd.currentnext, (((b.name::text || ' '::text) || ba.accountno::text) || ' No.'::text) || COALESCE(bd.currentnext, '-1'::integer::numeric) AS info, bd.c_bankaccountdoc_id from c_bankaccount ba inner join c_bank b on ba.c_bank_ID = b.c_bank_ID left join c_bankaccountdoc bd on ba.c_bankaccount_ID = bd.c_bankaccount_ID

PO.Data: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients. Tenant is a synonym for Client.
An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.
The record is active in the system

There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.
The Updated field indicates the date that this record was updated.
The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.
The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.

"A surrogate key in a database is a unique identifier for either an entity in the modeled world or an object in the database. The surrogate key is not derived from application data, unlike a natural (or business) key which is derived from application data. " , According to Wikipedia http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surrogate_key
The name of an entity (record) is used as an default search option in addition to the search key. The name is up to 60 characters in length.
The Account Number indicates the Number assigned to this bank account.
The Payment Rule indicates the method of invoice payment.
The Bank Account identifies an account at this Bank.
Bank Type define a type of bank or behavior
The Bank is a unique identifier of a Bank for this Organization or for a Business Partner with whom this Organization transacts.
The next number to be used
The Current Next indicates the next number to use for this document
